WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.237
Family is the ultimate power
on The Gifted.

00:03.271 --> 00:05.573
A lot of people
have been fighting this fight
for a long time,

00:05.606 --> 00:07.141
and now it's our turn.

00:07.175 --> 00:08.976
Catch all-new episodes Mondays.

00:09.009 --> 00:10.711
And check out our other
Fox programs-- The Orville,

00:10.744 --> 00:12.546
Lucifer, and Gotham.

00:12.580 --> 00:14.715
Gotham needs more people
who are willing
to fight for her.

00:14.748 --> 00:15.749
Only on Fox.

00:18.619 --> 00:19.753
DISPATCHER (over radio):
Attention all units:

00:19.787 --> 00:21.689
fugitive suspect spotted

00:21.722 --> 00:23.491
at Grand and 17th.
(siren wailing)

00:23.524 --> 00:24.892
MALE OFFICER:
Unit 2325 responding.

00:24.925 --> 00:26.026
Just approaching
the intersect.

00:26.060 --> 00:27.027
Heading there now.

00:27.061 --> 00:30.198
(tires squealing)

00:35.869 --> 00:38.206
Unit 1835, we have a
visual on the suspect

00:38.239 --> 00:39.940
heading east towards
Wellington.

00:39.973 --> 00:41.275
Copy that.

00:41.309 --> 00:42.443
Coming up on Wellington now.

00:42.476 --> 00:45.546
(siren wailing)

00:48.048 --> 00:51.352
(siren wailing)

00:51.385 --> 00:53.454
(tires squeal)

00:56.157 --> 00:58.192
(panting)

00:58.226 --> 01:01.229
(distant siren blaring)

01:01.262 --> 01:03.264
Come on. Come on!

01:03.297 --> 01:05.133
(tires squealing)
OFFICER (over loudspeaker):
On the ground now!

01:05.166 --> 01:06.967
Please.
OFFICER:
Put your hands on your head.

01:07.000 --> 01:09.036
Come on. (grunts) Come on!

01:09.069 --> 01:11.672
(electrical trilling,
woman gasping)

01:16.644 --> 01:18.879
(gasps)

01:18.912 --> 01:20.114
Stop! Stop!

01:20.148 --> 01:21.882
(tires squeak,
hissing, whooshing)

01:21.915 --> 01:25.553
(glass clinking)

01:25.586 --> 01:26.887
What the...?

01:26.920 --> 01:28.456
(pops, crackles)

01:28.489 --> 01:30.458
(train horn droning)

01:30.491 --> 01:34.762
(dog barking)

01:36.664 --> 01:38.232
You getting anything?

01:38.266 --> 01:39.733
Working on it.

01:39.767 --> 01:41.769
Yeah, you seriously think
she's here, man?

01:41.802 --> 01:44.338
I mean, she was just
two miles away.

01:45.273 --> 01:47.841
(ding, whoosh)

01:47.875 --> 01:51.245
(siren blaring, panting)

01:51.279 --> 01:52.613
She's close.

01:52.646 --> 01:55.082
Closer than the last time
she was close?

01:55.115 --> 01:56.217
(laughs)

01:58.952 --> 02:02.623
She's moving...
strangely.

02:02.656 --> 02:04.091
Yeah, I'm pretty sure

02:04.124 --> 02:05.859
he just likes
keeping us out in the cold.

02:05.893 --> 02:07.461
(laughs)

02:10.998 --> 02:12.800
(high-pitched tone sounds)

02:12.833 --> 02:15.303
Look.

02:15.336 --> 02:17.738
(soft, high-pitched tone
sounding)

02:20.574 --> 02:23.777
There.

02:23.811 --> 02:25.546
Well, that's
interesting.

02:25.579 --> 02:26.747
Told ya.

02:31.352 --> 02:33.721
Hey, you all right?

02:33.754 --> 02:35.122
Want me
to warm you up?
I'm okay.

02:35.155 --> 02:37.157
You can warm me
up later, though.

02:37.191 --> 02:38.992
Oh, I'm gonna
hold you to that.

02:47.167 --> 02:49.503
She's there.

02:49.537 --> 02:50.704
Inside.

02:52.340 --> 02:55.909
(thudding, rattling)

03:00.748 --> 03:04.552
Hey... go.

03:10.258 --> 03:13.861
(woman panting loudly)

03:13.894 --> 03:16.029
It's okay. We're
just gonna talk. Oh.
(gasps)

03:16.063 --> 03:18.499
Okay. Well,
hey, hold up.
(grunts)

03:18.532 --> 03:20.501
No. Wait a minute!

03:20.534 --> 03:22.403
Okay. Whoa. Whoa.

03:22.436 --> 03:23.604
(panting)

03:23.637 --> 03:24.872
Calm down, all right?

03:24.905 --> 03:26.674
You with the cops?

03:26.707 --> 03:28.442
I can't go back.

03:28.476 --> 03:30.778
We're not cops, okay?
We heard you broke out

03:30.811 --> 03:32.546
of the mutant detention
center and we came looking.

03:32.580 --> 03:34.014
I don't understand.

03:34.047 --> 03:35.783
Who are you?

03:38.286 --> 03:41.121
Just a couple of
freaks, same as you.

03:43.657 --> 03:45.859
Look, I'm Marcos,
this is Lorna.

03:45.893 --> 03:49.363
Now, trust me, we have all been
where you are, or worse.

03:49.397 --> 03:51.131
We can help.

03:51.164 --> 03:53.367
Now come with us.

03:53.401 --> 03:56.837
We can get you
some place safe...
Guys!

03:57.905 --> 03:59.139
There's trouble.

03:59.172 --> 04:00.541
Come on, get dressed.

04:00.574 --> 04:03.143
You're with us now.

04:04.345 --> 04:05.879
MARCOS:
What is it?

04:05.913 --> 04:08.248
MAN:
Cops. Coming
fast this way.

04:08.282 --> 04:09.483
Kill the lights.

04:09.517 --> 04:11.285
How many?
(whooshing)

04:11.319 --> 04:13.954
At least ten,
from the west and south.

04:13.987 --> 04:17.157
(sirens blaring)

04:17.190 --> 04:19.293
(tires squealing)

04:22.262 --> 04:25.265
OFFICER (over loudspeaker):
This is the Atlanta
Police Department.

04:25.299 --> 04:27.801
We know the fugitive is
in the building.

04:27.835 --> 04:30.137
Come out now,
or we will open fire.

04:31.505 --> 04:33.307
OFFICER 2:
The window!

04:33.341 --> 04:34.642
One suspect
at the window!

04:34.675 --> 04:37.144
(whooshing, whirring,
popping)

04:37.177 --> 04:39.847
(indistinct,
overlapping chatter)

04:39.880 --> 04:41.315
OFFICER:
Open fire!

04:41.349 --> 04:45.285
(gunfire,
glass breaking)

04:50.991 --> 04:54.261
Lorna!
I'm fine.
Find us a way out!

04:54.294 --> 04:55.996
(glass breaking)

04:57.197 --> 04:58.966
(gunfire)

04:58.999 --> 05:03.837
(glass breaking)

05:03.871 --> 05:05.873
(indistinct shouting)

05:06.807 --> 05:08.275
(gasps, mutters)

05:08.308 --> 05:09.309
(grunting)

05:13.013 --> 05:14.281
(indistinct shouting)

05:14.314 --> 05:15.649
Lorna! Get out of there!

05:16.884 --> 05:19.286
Go! Go!

05:19.319 --> 05:21.288
(high-pitched trilling)

05:21.321 --> 05:24.392
(man groaning)

05:24.425 --> 05:26.460
(high-pitched trill)

05:26.494 --> 05:29.930
Come on! Over here!

05:31.264 --> 05:33.033
(gunshot)

05:33.066 --> 05:34.635
(Marcos groans)

05:34.668 --> 05:36.203
LORNA:
Marcos!

05:36.236 --> 05:37.671
(yells)
God!

05:38.772 --> 05:41.174
(groans)

05:42.376 --> 05:44.812
(Lorna roaring)

05:44.845 --> 05:47.548
Lorna! Come back!

05:47.581 --> 05:48.916
Come, come back!

05:50.918 --> 05:52.319
(yelling)

05:52.352 --> 05:53.987
Freeze!
(Lorna groaning,
electrical hissing)

05:54.021 --> 05:55.355
(Lorna screaming)

05:55.389 --> 05:57.658
(electricity crackles,
man groans)

05:57.691 --> 06:00.327
MARCOS:
Lorna! Stop!

06:00.360 --> 06:02.730
LORNA: No!
OFFICER: Put your hands
behind your back!

06:02.763 --> 06:05.666
Marcos!
Lorna!

06:05.699 --> 06:08.602
*

06:08.636 --> 06:12.239
MAN: I understand
you have some concerns

06:12.272 --> 06:14.274
about your son, Andy?

06:14.307 --> 06:16.343
Yes, we believe
he's being bullied.

06:16.376 --> 06:18.011
Belleview High has

06:18.045 --> 06:20.514
a zero tolerance policy
towards bullying.

06:20.548 --> 06:22.416
That's why we came.

06:22.450 --> 06:26.420
Um, Andy and I have always been
very close, but lately he...

06:26.454 --> 06:30.223
he just stopped
talking to me.

06:30.257 --> 06:31.725
It's affecting his grades.

06:31.759 --> 06:33.360
He-He's not sleeping.

06:33.393 --> 06:35.128
In situations
like this,

06:35.162 --> 06:39.199
we like to use
the "CARE" system-- communicate,

06:39.232 --> 06:41.469
adjust, reconcile

06:41.502 --> 06:44.137
and empathize. First,
we take the kids,

06:44.171 --> 06:46.273
and we put them together
to talk.

06:46.306 --> 06:48.408
These boys are-are
tormenting our son.

06:48.442 --> 06:49.877
I understand that's upsetting.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.378
Stop right there.
Let me be clear.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.881
Andy needs help,

06:53.914 --> 06:58.118
and if he doesn't get it, I will
sue this school into oblivion.

06:58.151 --> 07:00.754
Mr. Strucker,

07:00.788 --> 07:02.790
we have procedures. I can't...

07:02.823 --> 07:04.792
Then get someone who can.

07:04.825 --> 07:06.293
Now.

07:10.531 --> 07:12.966
Okay, I'll-I'll be right back.

07:14.668 --> 07:16.269
(door opens)

07:16.303 --> 07:20.007
Wow. Scary.

07:20.040 --> 07:21.742
(chuckles)
Was it too much?

07:21.775 --> 07:24.144
I felt like the glaring was
a little over the top.
No.

07:24.177 --> 07:26.346
That was the perfect
amount of glaring.

07:26.379 --> 07:28.048
(phone buzzes)

07:30.518 --> 07:32.953
Ugh. I got to go
to Garland.

07:32.986 --> 07:34.522
Plea conference
with a suspect.

07:34.555 --> 07:37.124
They need me there ASAP.

07:37.157 --> 07:38.626
Will you tell the kids
I'm really sorry?

07:38.659 --> 07:40.027
I'll be back tomorrow.

07:40.060 --> 07:41.461
The kids understand.

07:41.495 --> 07:43.430
You're keeping us safe.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.699
I love you.

07:45.733 --> 07:47.535
I love you, too.

07:49.469 --> 07:53.073
Bye.
Bye.

07:56.677 --> 07:59.212
* If I told you
I loved you... *

07:59.246 --> 08:00.981
You have no preference?

08:01.014 --> 08:02.850
They are two
completely different outfits.

08:02.883 --> 08:04.451
I don't know. I'm sorry.

08:04.484 --> 08:05.553
You look good in both.

08:05.586 --> 08:06.854
Not helpful, Jack.

08:06.887 --> 08:08.455
Now just pick an outfit.

08:08.488 --> 08:09.857
(sighs)
I don't know. Um...

08:09.890 --> 08:11.659
CAITLIN:
Lauren, I'm home.

08:11.692 --> 08:13.894
The blue one. Do the blue one.

08:13.927 --> 08:15.395
That one looks nice.

08:15.428 --> 08:17.464
Also, uh, do you want me
to pick you up?

08:17.497 --> 08:18.999
Because it's no problem.

08:19.032 --> 08:20.668
No, but I'll push
for an 11:30 curfew.

08:20.701 --> 08:22.870
I'll see you tonight.
Bye.

08:22.903 --> 08:24.471
So, Lauren,
how was choir?

08:24.504 --> 08:27.641
Good. We're practicing
for the spring concert.

08:27.675 --> 08:28.809
Are you still going
to the dance tonight?

08:28.842 --> 08:32.546
Want me to show you
some of my moves?

08:32.580 --> 08:34.582
No, thank you.
(laughs)

08:36.784 --> 08:38.385
How about you?
How was your day?

08:38.418 --> 08:39.920
Uh, bad.

08:40.621 --> 08:41.989
I mean, you were there.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.390
(laughs)

08:43.423 --> 08:45.225
I meant your classes.

08:45.258 --> 08:46.860
Anything interesting?

08:46.894 --> 08:49.062
We had a debate
in social studies about the law

08:49.096 --> 08:51.231
they want to make
to test people with the X-gene

08:51.264 --> 08:52.566
and, like, monitor
them. I don't know.

08:52.600 --> 08:54.835
Anyway, this one kid
was, like, freaking out.

08:54.868 --> 08:56.169
I guess his cousin's
a mutie or something.

08:56.203 --> 08:59.239
Mutie, Andy? Racist much?

08:59.272 --> 09:01.408
What?
Person of genetic difference.

09:01.441 --> 09:02.743
You are such an ass!

09:02.776 --> 09:04.077
Okay, please.
You're fighting

09:04.111 --> 09:06.046
about social studies
class now.

09:06.079 --> 09:08.616
Can we not have
a normal conversation?

09:12.586 --> 09:15.188
(sighs)
Guess not.

09:15.222 --> 09:17.825
(lock buzzes)

09:20.460 --> 09:22.763
Ms. Dane?

09:22.796 --> 09:25.132
My name is Reed Strucker.

09:25.165 --> 09:27.601
This is my associate,
Carla Jackson.

09:27.635 --> 09:31.639
I'd offer you a seat,
but, uh, you know.

09:31.672 --> 09:34.207
You're accused of the attempted
murder of two police officers.

09:34.241 --> 09:37.144
That
plus the enhanced sentencing

09:37.177 --> 09:39.546
for the use
of your mutant abilities.

09:39.579 --> 09:41.048
Equals I'm screwed.

09:41.081 --> 09:43.083
Yeah, I got that.

09:43.116 --> 09:45.919
We can reduce the charges

09:45.953 --> 09:47.755
in exchange
for your cooperation.

09:47.788 --> 09:50.290
Look, all I know is,
I was walking in the rain,

09:50.323 --> 09:52.459
and some cops shot at me.

09:52.492 --> 09:56.596
Come on, Ms. Dane.

09:56.630 --> 09:58.465
You and your associates

09:58.498 --> 10:02.502
in the mutant underground
have aided and abetted dozens,

10:02.535 --> 10:06.139
if not hundreds, of fugitives.

10:12.880 --> 10:14.147
(trilling)

10:14.181 --> 10:16.684
Reed.
It's okay.

10:18.986 --> 10:23.556
(high-pitched,
rhythmic trilling)

10:28.729 --> 10:30.931
Believe it or not,
I'm trying to help you.

10:30.964 --> 10:33.500
These are serious charges.

10:33.533 --> 10:35.068
Attempted murder...

10:36.737 --> 10:39.840
(hissing)

10:39.873 --> 10:44.311
(groans)
Those screws in your
knee-- old sports injury?

10:44.344 --> 10:45.612
(groans)
If I wanted to,

10:45.645 --> 10:47.280
I could tear out those screws

10:47.314 --> 10:50.017
and show you
some attempted murder.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.885
(groans)

10:51.919 --> 10:56.389
Believe me, if I wanted
those cops dead, they'd be dead.

11:01.061 --> 11:03.831
There's a factor
you may not be aware of.

11:08.201 --> 11:12.205
I am gonna ask the court

11:12.239 --> 11:15.175
to assign you a lawyer, okay?

11:17.410 --> 11:19.880
You've got a big decision
to make, Ms. Dane.

11:19.913 --> 11:21.581
Son of a bitch.

11:23.416 --> 11:26.519
No, no, no, no.

11:26.553 --> 11:28.088
No.
(sobs)

11:28.121 --> 11:29.890
No! No!

11:29.923 --> 11:32.192
(shouting)

11:35.362 --> 11:36.463
(cries)

11:38.265 --> 11:40.433
Give it some thought.

11:46.573 --> 11:48.375
CAITLIN:
Be home at 11:30!

11:48.408 --> 11:50.811
I know, I know. I love you.

12:01.588 --> 12:02.790
Yo.

12:02.823 --> 12:04.391
What are you doing here?

12:04.424 --> 12:06.726
I snuck out.
I thought I'd go with you.

12:06.760 --> 12:08.595
Didn't you tell Mom
you were going to bed?

12:08.628 --> 12:11.131
Yeah, that's why they call it
sneaking. Can we go?

12:11.164 --> 12:12.900
You can't.
What if she finds out?

12:12.933 --> 12:14.301
If I get caught, I'll tell her
I was going down to Ian's.

12:14.334 --> 12:15.302
You won't get in trouble.

12:15.335 --> 12:16.636
When was the last time

12:16.669 --> 12:18.705
I got to go out on a weekend?

12:18.738 --> 12:19.940
It's like I'm a...

12:19.973 --> 12:22.609
one-one of those baby cows
they keep in the crates.

12:22.642 --> 12:24.211
Veal?

12:24.244 --> 12:27.547
Yeah. I'm being raised
like a veal.

12:27.580 --> 12:30.383
You really want
to go to a dance?

12:30.417 --> 12:33.586
After everything
that's been going on at school?

12:33.620 --> 12:35.755
You mean my fan club?

12:35.789 --> 12:39.426
(sighs) Yeah, whatever.
I'm used to them.

12:40.460 --> 12:42.662
(groans)

12:42.695 --> 12:43.931
Buckle up.

12:43.964 --> 12:45.732
(starts engine)

12:45.765 --> 12:48.135
*

